      "assess": "Contusion size was calculated using CT scans analyzed with 3D Slicer software (version 4.8.0). Regions of interest were manually selected, and a fixed Hounsfield unit threshold (50–110 HU) was applied to identify contused tissue. The software automatically calculated the volume by summing adjacent voxels. Volumes >13.5 ml are associated with higher PTE risk (61 points)."
