      "assess": "Non-LPTS refers to seizures occurring within seven days of traumatic brain injury (TBI), including Immediate Post-Traumatic Seizures (IPTS, within 24 hours) and Early Post-Traumatic Seizures (EPTS, 24 hours to seven days). The presence of Non-LPTS significantly increases the risk of Post-Traumatic Epilepsy (PTE), with a risk score of 76 points."
